1984	[(S3.sep.1) Smooth proper schemes have geometrically reduced global sections]
1985	  \label{lem:S3_sep_1_smooth_geometrically_reduced_Gamma}
1986	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.isGeometricallyReduced_Gamma_of_smooth}
1987	  Let $X$ be a smooth proper scheme over a field $k$. Then the global-section $k$-algebra $\Gamma(X, \mathcal O_X)$ is geometrically reduced over $k$, i.e.\ \texttt{Algebra.IsGeometricallyReduced}\,$k$\,$\Gamma(X, \mathcal O_X)$.
